<paragraph blockId="127.[128,654,542,949]" pageId="127" pageNumber="127">
COMMENTS: Hartert based his description on a single male specimen from Yelwa, but said that another specimen from Rabba on the 
<collectingCountry box="[176,242,780,802]" name="Niger" pageId="127" pageNumber="127">Niger</collectingCountry>
in BMNH probably belonged to the same taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="127.[128,654,542,949]" pageId="127" pageNumber="127">
Hartert used the spelling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1872" box="[447,586,839,862]" class="Aves" family="Viduidae" genus="Hypochaera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="127" pageNumber="127" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[447,586,839,862]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="127">Hypochaera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his description of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hartert" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[296,412,868,891]" class="Aves" family="Viduidae" genus="Vidua" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="127" pageNumber="127" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wilsoni">
<emphasis box="[296,412,868,891]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="127">H. wilsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a full species, not as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[348,482,898,920]" class="Aves" family="Viduidae" genus="Hypochaera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="127" pageNumber="127" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="furnerea">
<emphasis box="[348,482,898,920]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="127">H. furnerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as in 
<bibRefCitation author="Fry, C. H. &amp; S. Keith" pageId="127" pageNumber="127" refId="ref116661" refString="Fry, C. H., and S. Keith (editors). 2004. The birds of Africa, vol. 7. Princeton, NJ: Princeton University Press, xxi + 666 pp., 36 pls." type="book" year="2004">Fry and Keith (2004: 439)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
